nodes.bodyText: If two or more of these started at the same time, there could be duplicates.  Would that be ok?  If not, you should also add a UUID here.
there is clearRegistries function that deletes the registries based on created Date (from oldest to new ones).
You might be better off using java-reg-UUID-TimeMillis.
Seems like overkill to have currentTimeMillis + uuid, why not just UUID()?
Hmm, I do not know why it was done this way, but I will just replace with just UUID()
